description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshcore/include/lichen/meshcore/adapter.h
Line: 126, 140-141

File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshcore/adapter.c
Line: 1193

The struct uses uint16_t for length fields:
```c
struct lichen_meshcore_pending_event {
    ...
    uint16_t payload_len;  // Line 126
    uint8_t payload[LICHEN_MESHCORE_FRAME_MAX];
};

struct lichen_meshcore_adapter {
    ...
    uint16_t stream_len;      // Line 140
    uint16_t stream_expected; // Line 141
};
```

But there is no BUILD_ASSERT ensuring LICHEN_MESHCORE_FRAME_MAX <= UINT16_MAX (65535).

At line 1193, the cast truncates silently:
```c
pending->payload_len = (uint16_t)event->payload_len;
```

If CONFIG_LICHEN_MESHCORE_MAX_FRAME > 65535, the payload_len field cannot represent all valid lengths, causing data corruption.

Fix: Add BUILD_ASSERT(LICHEN_MESHCORE_FRAME_MAX <= UINT16_MAX, "Frame max exceeds uint16_t limit");
